Co-written by Dr Tony Valsamakis, Prof Robert Vivian, Dr GS du Toit, and Prof J Young, this new edition of Risk Management sees the authors build on their unique and respected model of risk management for students, academics, and professionals. At the launch, which was hosted in Sandton CBD on 10 March 2022, Dr Valsamakis said: “It is a pleasure and honour to celebrate the publication of this fifth edition with so many esteemed colleagues and friends, especially after the travails of restrictions wrought by Covid over the last 2-odd years. It is especially relevant to be speaking about risk management at this precarious juncture in time with so many challenges facing us as a global society – the effects of a pandemic and a war in Europe.”In the context of a fast-moving and ever-evolving business landscape, the fifth edition of Risk Management introduces the following: an update of the impact of legislation and corporate governance on the discipline;  an update of the King VI Code;a new section on banking risk;  financial instruments update;  the evolution and development of risk financing, following the changes in economic and financial market environments;  a section on sustainable risk; andmanaging the financial impact of COVID-19 as a pandemicThis textbook is targeted at students who are enrolled in risk management, safety management, financial management and insurance courses at university level. However, Dr Valsamakis  believes this can also form an essential part of any risk management professional’s library.“This book remains the authoritative South African publication on a subject that has exponentially increased in these unpredictable and risk laden times,” says Dr Valsamakis. The book will be available for purchase from Van Schaik Bookstore and other leading textbook shops and an e-book version will be on the Pearson e-store and through Pearson’s e-book distribution partners. Pearson offers a comprehensive range of e-books in multiple formats, to effectively support the teaching and learning process for school, TVET and higher education institutions. Janet Naudé, product manager: Higher Ed and TVET at Pearson South Africa says: “With a focus on employability and getting students ready for the world of work, we partner with authors, lecturers and students to continually improve the learning materials, digital solutions and services we provide for use at higher education institutions and TVET colleges throughout South Africa.” Naude’ is proud to have influential titles, such as the fifth edition of Risk Management, forming a critical part of the Pearson's offering and says we will endeavor to continue providing South African students and professionals the best service that we can. To learn more about how Pearson is enhancing digital education at every level, visit the new and improved Pearson eStore.